# Licensing for content-model/

While this directory lives in the contentRX monorepo it is governed by
the **root LICENSE** ([Functional Source License, FSL-1.1-MIT](../LICENSE)),
not by Creative Commons. The standards library, moments taxonomy, and
associated specification documents here are part of the same
source-available product as the engine, web app, and surfaces.

## Future intent

If/when this directory is published as the standalone
`contentrx-standards` repository (BUILD_PLAN_v2 Sessions 19 and 20,
currently deferred per the
[2026-04-25 private-taxonomy pivot ADR](../decisions/2026-04-25-private-taxonomy-pivot.md)),
the spec content is intended to ship under
**Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)** so
external users can adopt and adapt the standards with attribution.

That re-licensing happens at the moment of publication, not now. Until
then, the FSL-1.1-MIT terms in the root LICENSE govern this content.

## Why this directory has its own LICENSE file

The file is preserved as reversibility insurance. The README in this
directory documents the deferred-spec-repo status; this LICENSE file
is the placeholder for the CC BY 4.0 grant that activates on
publication. Don't delete it.

---

For the operative license that applies to this content right now, see
[../LICENSE](../LICENSE).
